---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import SEOHead from '../components/SEOHead.astro';
import { url } from '../utils/paths';
---
<Base title="Services — Fractional CMO, Strategic Advisor, Build and Hand Over" description="Three ways to engage Manual Focus — Strategic Advisor, Fractional CMO, Build and Hand Over — plus Manual Focus AI, our product for done-for-you AI marketing workflows.">
  <SEOHead slot="seo" type="service" title="Services — Fractional CMO and AI marketing workflows" description="Three ways to engage Manual Focus — Strategic Advisor, Fractional CMO, Build and Hand Over — plus Manual Focus AI for done-for-you AI workflows." breadcrumbs={[{ name: 'Home', url: '/' }, { name: 'Services', url: '/services' }]} />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container reveal">
      <div class="eyebrow">SERVICES</div>
      <h1>How we work together</h1>
      <p class="lead">Three ways to engage with the team, all of them threading AI and emerging tech into the workflows you already run. Plus one product where Manual Focus owns and runs the AI workflows on your behalf.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Strategic Advisor -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-detail reveal">
        <div class="service-tag mono">/01 · STRATEGIC ADVISOR</div>
        <h2>The senior voice in the room</h2>
        <p class="service-for">For companies with a marketing team but no senior leader running it.</p>
        <p>You have people doing the work. What you don't have is someone senior calling the shots, reviewing the output and asking the harder questions. We sit alongside the team for a handful of sessions a month, giving you the strategic input of a CMO without the cost or commitment of one.</p>

        <h3>What this looks like</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Weekly or fortnightly working sessions on what to do next</li>
          <li>Reviews of campaigns, content and creative before they ship</li>
          <li>Quarterly planning and priority-setting with the team</li>
          <li>Briefings on the AI tooling and emerging tech worth using, and where it fits the workflows your team already runs</li>
          <li>Hiring and team-shape advice as you grow the function</li>
          <li>Direct line between sessions for the calls that won't wait</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>What this is not</h3>
        <p>We won't run your team for you, ship the work on your behalf, or sit in every meeting. This is senior input on a part-time cadence, not embedded leadership.</p>

        <p class="service-shape mono">Shape · 1–2 days a month. Day rate or monthly retainer.</p>
        <a href={url('/enquire')} class="btn-cta" style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">Book a session</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Fractional CMO -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-detail reveal">
        <div class="service-tag mono">/02 · FRACTIONAL CMO</div>
        <h2>Embedded senior marketer</h2>
        <p class="service-for">For companies that need senior marketing leadership without a full-time hire.</p>
        <p>We embed in your leadership team. We set the marketing thesis, build the plan, lead the people you already have, and ship the pieces that need senior hands. AI and emerging tech are wired into the workflows your team already runs, so a small team moves like a much larger one. You get the seniority of a CMO at a fraction of the cost, with execution shipped alongside the strategy.</p>

        <h3>What this looks like</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Marketing thesis, 90-day plan and quarterly OKRs</li>
          <li>Leading and growing the existing team (or hiring it)</li>
          <li>Embedding AI and emerging tech into the workflows your team already runs, day by day</li>
          <li>Shipping key campaigns, launches and content with that leverage in place</li>
          <li>Owning reporting to the CEO and board</li>
          <li>Inputs into product, pricing and positioning decisions</li>
          <li>Bringing the Forge tooling to compress production cycles</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>What this is not</h3>
        <p>This isn't a generalist consultant who hands you a deck. It's senior marketing leadership that ships work. And it's not unlimited time. The seat is part-time by design, so the cadence has to be set up to make the most of it.</p>

        <p class="service-shape mono">Shape · 1–2 days a week. Three-month minimum.</p>
        <a href={url('/enquire')} class="btn-cta" style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">Book a session</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Build & Hand Over -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-detail reveal">
        <div class="service-tag mono">/03 · BUILD &amp; HAND OVER</div>
        <h2>Scoped outcome, shipped fast</h2>
        <p class="service-for">For companies that know what they need built, and want it shipped fast.</p>
        <p>You have a specific marketing outcome in mind, whether that's a launch, a website rebuild, an SEO program, a brand refresh or a content engine. We build it end-to-end with AI and emerging tech wired into the build (not bolted on after), then hand it back to your team to operate, with documentation and training to keep it running.</p>

        <h3>What this looks like</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Product or feature launches, with positioning, narrative and assets</li>
          <li>Commerce rebuilds on Shopify, BigCommerce or WooCommerce/WordPress — full-stack or headless, shipped fast</li>
          <li>Headless web architectures — composable stacks built for speed, SEO and a clean handover</li>
          <li>Landing systems and conversion infrastructure (Next, Astro, Webflow where it fits)</li>
          <li>SEO and answer-engine optimisation programs, including content engines</li>
          <li>Brand refreshes with messaging architecture and visual direction</li>
          <li>PR campaigns with journalist outreach, story arcs and placement</li>
          <li>AI and emerging-tech workflows embedded into your existing stack, not a parallel one</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>What this is not</h3>
        <p>It's not a retainer dressed up as a project. The scope is fixed up front, the price is fixed up front, and the handover is real. After it's shipped, your team owns it.</p>

        <p class="service-shape mono">Shape · Fixed scope, fixed timeline, fixed price. Typical builds 4–12 weeks.</p>
        <a href={url('/enquire')} class="btn-cta" style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">Book a session</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- /04 Manual Focus AI · the product -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-detail service-detail-product reveal">
        <div class="service-tag mono">/04 · MANUAL FOCUS · AI <span class="service-tag-flag">PRODUCT</span></div>
        <h2>We run the AI workflows. You get the output.</h2>
        <p class="service-for">For CTOs, CMOs and existing teams who can't carve out the time to stay current with new models, build pipelines or learn another tool every week.</p>
        <p>Manual Focus AI is the product side of the agency. Instead of teaching your team to run the workflows, we own them. Content planning, wireframing and production sit inside Manual Focus, run on the Forge, and the output lands in your stack on an agreed cadence. When a new model ships that's better than the one we were using, we swap it in. You don't see any of that, you just keep getting better output.</p>

        <h3>What this looks like</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Content planning pipelines — calendars, briefs, drafts, fact-checks</li>
          <li>Wireframing and creative production — landing pages, ad units, social packs</li>
          <li>Research and synthesis — competitor moves, SERP shifts, model launches, distilled weekly</li>
          <li>Pipelines maintained and re-tooled as new models and capabilities ship</li>
          <li>Output delivered in your brand and your stack, ready to use, not just ready to edit</li>
          <li>No internal training, no tool sprawl, no learning curve for your team</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>What this is not</h3>
        <p>It's not headcount you have to manage. It's not a tool you have to learn. It's not a generic SaaS subscription. The workflows are owned and operated by Manual Focus, tuned to your brand and your priorities, and the output shows up on cadence.</p>

        <p class="service-shape mono">Shape · Monthly retainer. Output on agreed cadence. Three-month minimum.</p>
        <a href={url('/enquire')} class="btn-cta" style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">Book a working session</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Specialism note -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container reveal">
      <div class="eyebrow">VERTICAL DEPTH</div>
      <h2 class="vertical-headline">Endurance and sports brands<br/>are where we've shipped the most.</h2>
      <p class="vertical-copy">If you're building in endurance, sports or the broader fitness category, you're getting a team that has run marketing in your category at scale. Our founder, James Vickers, co-founded RGT Cycling and took it from 19k to 350k users before Wahoo Fitness acquired it. Beyond that, we've led marketing across AI, fintech, hardware and digital assets, so the playbook travels.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .lead {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    max-width: 760px;
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .service-detail {
    max-width: var(--max-width);
  }

  /* Product tier — distinct from the three engagement tiers above */
  .service-detail-product {
    position: relative;
    padding: var(--space-md);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-line);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(192, 38, 211, 0.05), rgba(0, 229, 255, 0.02)),
      var(--color-bg);
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .service-detail-product::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
    height: 3px;
    background: var(--color-cta-gradient);
  }
  .service-tag-flag {
    margin-left: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.15rem 0.55rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-cta-end);
    color: var(--color-cta-end);
    border-radius: 999px;
    font-size: 0.625rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    background: rgba(0, 229, 255, 0.06);
    vertical-align: middle;
  }
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .service-detail-product { padding: var(--space-lg); }
  }

  .service-tag {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .service-for {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .service-detail > p {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: var(--font-size-body);
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .service-detail h3 {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-size: var(--font-size-body);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .service-detail ul {
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
    padding-left: var(--space-md);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .service-detail ul li {
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .service-shape {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    padding-top: var(--space-sm);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-line);
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .vertical-headline {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    line-height: 1;
    max-width: 900px;
  }

  .vertical-copy {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 760px;
  }
</style>
